title: Undecided Democrats break in favor of Iran deal, likely forestalling need for Obama veto
text:
09 Undecided Democrats break in favor of Iran deal, likely forestalling need for Obama veto 
The Washington Post: A band of undecided Senate Democrats broke in favor of the international nuclear deal with Iran on Tuesday, putting President Obama on the brink of one of the most significant victories of his presidency.Forty-two senators are now publicly supportive of the Iran deal, all of them Democrats or independents who caucus with Democrats. That would be enough to bottle up Republican attempts to overturn the deal, sparing Obama the drama and embarrassment of having to veto legislation rejecting it.
